Sizzling songstress Ayra Starr has refuted rumour of dating her colleague, Rema, stating he’s simply her brother in Christ. Generally speaking, a brother in Christ refers to another Christian who is considered to be a close friend or family member.  This term is often used to describe someone who has shared similar experiences or who provides support and encouragement in one’s faith journey. Celestial being referred to Rema as ‘brother in Christ’ during a recent interview with Kenya’s Kiss FM when queried about the dating rumours involving herself and the Rave Lorde. “I don’t know. I haven’t heard that before,” said the “Sability” crooner in response to the question. Offering more clarity on their relationship, Starr added: “That’s my brother in Christ o.”